docs: Returns the address of the current owner.
messages.label: Ownable::owner

docs: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call
owner's functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.
NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner,
thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.
On success a `OwnershipTransferred` event is emitted.
Panics with `CallerIsNotOwner` error if caller is not owner
messages.label: Ownable::renounce_ownership

docs: Transfers ownership of the contract to a `new_owner`.
Can only be called by the current owner.
On success a `OwnershipTransferred` event is emitted.
Panics with `CallerIsNotOwner` error if caller is not owner.
Panics with `NewOwnerIsZero` error if new owner's address is zero.
messages.label: Ownable::transfer_ownership

docs: This function allow contract owner modifies the code which is used to execute calls to this contract address (`AccountId`).
